comments.content:
Without Flashback data archive (default configuration):
SQL> insert into t1 values (1);
1 row created.

SQL> commit;
Commit complete.

SQL> select current_scn from v$database;
CURRENT_SCN
-----------
 1754160

SQL> truncate table t1;
Table truncated.

SQL> flashback table t1 to SCN 1754160;
flashback table t1 to SCN 1754160
 *
ERROR at line 1:
ORA-01466: unable to read data - table definition has changed

And the same error occurs after creating flashback data archive:
SQL> CREATE FLASHBACK ARCHIVE DEFAULT mytest TABLESPACE users Quota 1M Retention 1 Day;
Flashback archive created.

and modifying t1 table to use it:
SQL> alter table t1 flashback archive;
Table altered.
